data.description: Situated at the top corner of a Cul de Sac, this home has potent street appeal, as well as the best lake view in Beekman Place. It is one of the larger homes and as such allows for the creation of both an office, and den/playroom, while providing a SEPARATE DINING ROOM, and FORMAL LIVING ROOM. Sip your morning coffee at the granite kitchen counter or better yet, on the lanai where you can also enjoy watching water birds and turtles frolic almost at your feet. If you have children visiting, put up the kid-proof fencing now resting in the OVERSIZED garage. And know that they won't have to traipse through the house to use the potty because the second full bath opens directly onto the lanai. The owners have chosen renewable Bamboo for the flooring (and it can be refreshed by sanding), ceramic tile, and BRICK PAVERS on the lanai, driveway and path. Newer stainless kitchen appliances, and cabinets featuring an abundance of PULL-OUT DRAWERS await your culinary input. The laundry room is equipped with tub, shelving and appliances. Freshly painted both inside and out, the home also has sidewalks all around the house, and HURRICANE FILM on all windows. WATER VIEWS FROM 5 ROOMS provide ever changing vistas. Easy-care year-round shrubs and flowers are in place, and finally have peace of mind for all systems with the owner provided one-year warranty from American Home Shield.
